# LLM calls: single gate (no bypass)

**Required architecture:**

```text
pipeline / feature code
   → safe_llm_call()                    # src/ops/llm_client.py — only doorway
        → assert_llm_call_allowed()       # BEFORE network I/O (see checklist below)
        → retry loop wraps llm_callable ONLY (max_llm_retries_per_call)
   → vendor API                          # ONLY inside llm_client (injected callable)
   → record_llm_usage()                  # actual tokens & cost when API returns them
   → record_spend_usd()                  # daily/month JSON under budget_persistence_dir
   → append_llm_ledger_entry()           # JSONL audit (allowed/blocked)
```

**Checklist inside `assert_llm_call_allowed` (order matters conceptually):** kill switch (`.llm_kill_switch`) → **`llm_enabled`** → prompt validation (`max_prompt_chars`, key-like strings, huge base64-like lines, optional substrings) → **`expected_output_tokens > 0`** → per-call cost vs **`max_estimated_cost_usd_per_call`** → persisted daily/month caps vs **`daily_usage_*.json` / `monthly_usage_*.json`** → run-level caps → **`dry_run`** refusal → **`allowed_models`** → **`ALLOW_REAL_LLM_CALLS=true`**.

**Forbidden:**

```text
retry(safe_llm_call(...))     # retries must not wrap the guard
pipeline code → vendor SDK directly
```

If any file can reach the API without going through `safe_llm_call`, it can bypass the guard.

**Fail-closed:** Default to **`llm_enabled`: false**, **`dry_run`: true**, **`fail_closed`: true**. Incomplete **`budget`** dict → error; no silent allowance.

**Persistence paths** (under **`budget_persistence_dir`**, e.g. `logs/budget`): **`daily_usage_YYYY-MM-DD.json`**, **`monthly_usage_YYYY-MM.json`**, **`ledger_YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl`**.

**Policy:** No raw vendor calls anywhere except inside the approved `llm_client` wrapper. **`safe_llm_call`** requires **`model`** and must enforce a strict output budget (**`expected_output_tokens`**); wire the vendor **`max_tokens`** (or equivalent) to that value in real integrations.

**Steelman (`speaker_perspective`):** Record **`speaker_perspective_use_llm`**, posture (**`speaker_perspective_llm_model`**, token/claim caps), **`speaker_perspective_llm_requested`**, **`speaker_perspective_llm_executed`**, plus **`llm_mode_attempted`**, **`llm_mode_used`**, **`fallback_used`**, and **`fallback_reason`** (empty string when no fallback). When **`use_llm: true`**, non-empty reasons include **`missing_budget_config`**, **`llm_call_failed`** (guard/vendor/error), **`llm_response_parse_failed`**, and **`llm_response_validation_failed`**.

**Estimates vs reality:** `estimate_tokens()` (chars÷4) is pre-flight only; prefer the target tokenizer when precision matters. **`record_llm_usage`** must receive **actual** usage/cost from the API when available.
